1
00:00:20,562 --> 00:00:25,817
[music playing]

2
00:02:46,958 --> 00:02:48,001
-How's the soup?

3
00:02:48,001 --> 00:02:50,921
-The soup is excellent.

4
00:02:50,921 --> 00:02:53,048
-You're a good man, Frank.

5
00:02:53,048 --> 00:02:55,092
One day I'm going
to pay you back

6
00:02:55,092 --> 00:02:56,343
for everything with interest.

7
00:02:58,970 --> 00:03:03,016
-I'm going to mention this
place to all my friends.

8
00:03:03,016 --> 00:03:04,601
-Do me a favor.

9
00:03:04,601 --> 00:03:06,103
Let's just keep it between us.

10
00:03:18,990 --> 00:03:22,369
[music playing]

11
00:03:41,721 --> 00:03:43,682
-Mambo Cafe.

12
00:03:43,682 --> 00:03:48,061
Look, I told you already,
the check is in the mail.

13
00:03:48,061 --> 00:03:49,646
How am I supposed
to pay you if you

14
00:03:49,646 --> 00:03:52,524
keep calling me all the time?

15
00:03:52,524 --> 00:03:55,152
I don't have time for this.

16
00:03:55,152 --> 00:03:56,570
This is a very busy place.

17
00:03:56,570 --> 00:03:59,823
I have a lot of hungry
customers hollering at me.

18
00:03:59,823 --> 00:04:03,034
They're hungry, they
need me to feed them.

19
00:04:03,034 --> 00:04:05,454
-Hey, am I going to get
any service over here?

20
00:04:05,454 --> 00:04:06,413
I want that special.

21
00:04:06,413 --> 00:04:08,665
And a side of rice and beans.

22
00:04:08,665 --> 00:04:10,834
-And give me an
order of that steak

23
00:04:10,834 --> 00:04:12,669
fillet with extra vegetables.

24
00:04:12,669 --> 00:04:14,171
Another double order--

25
00:04:14,171 --> 00:04:16,673
-Look, call me
later, in three days,

26
00:04:16,673 --> 00:04:18,175
if you haven't
gotten it yet, OK?

27
00:04:18,175 --> 00:04:19,509
Bye.

28
00:04:19,509 --> 00:04:22,596
-I think we should talk again
about what I said yesterday.

29
00:04:22,596 --> 00:04:25,307
-Look, I told you I don't
want to have no more talking

30
00:04:25,307 --> 00:04:28,768
about going back to Puerto Rico.

31
00:04:28,768 --> 00:04:30,687
Why is it that every
time a Puerto Rican has

32
00:04:30,687 --> 00:04:32,314
a little problem
over here, they take

33
00:04:32,314 --> 00:04:34,691
a $99 flight back
to Puerto Rico?

34
00:04:34,691 --> 00:04:35,901
They have a problem over there?

35
00:04:35,901 --> 00:04:38,570
They take another $99
flight back to the States.

36
00:04:38,570 --> 00:04:41,281
Did you ever see the
Greeks or the Jews

37
00:04:41,281 --> 00:04:43,909
or the Italians
running back and forth

38
00:04:43,909 --> 00:04:45,660
every time things
got a little tough?

39
00:04:45,660 --> 00:04:46,786
No.

40
00:04:46,786 --> 00:04:48,914
It was too and it
was too expensive.

41
00:04:48,914 --> 00:04:50,707
So they planted their
feet in America,

42
00:04:50,707 --> 00:04:53,877
and that's why they made it.

43
00:04:53,877 --> 00:04:55,337
Sometimes I think the
biggest problem we

44
00:04:55,337 --> 00:04:58,757
Puerto Rican have is
those damn $99 fares.

45
00:04:58,757 --> 00:05:01,134
-You want to know what I think
is the biggest problem we have?

46
00:05:01,134 --> 00:05:02,552
-Not really.

47
00:05:02,552 --> 00:05:06,890
-It's hard-headed men like you
who are too stubborn to realize

48
00:05:06,890 --> 00:05:10,894
that it's better to struggle
on a beautiful tropical island

49
00:05:10,894 --> 00:05:13,814
than in some ghetto
in the United States.

50
00:05:13,814 --> 00:05:15,857
-I told you a hundred
times already.

51
00:05:15,857 --> 00:05:19,319
The only way I'm going back
to Puerto Rico is as a success

52
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:20,278
or in a pine box.

53
00:05:20,278 --> 00:05:21,905
-Well you better
make it pretty quick

54
00:05:21,905 --> 00:05:23,073
because in another
week all we're

55
00:05:23,073 --> 00:05:25,700
going to be able to
afford is cardboard.

56
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:27,244
-Oh, hi, Ma.

57
00:05:27,244 --> 00:05:28,119
How you doin', Pop?

58
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:29,788
-Hey.

59
00:05:29,788 --> 00:05:31,748
Pull up those pants.

60
00:05:31,748 --> 00:05:33,166
What have you got there?

61
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:35,377
-What?

62
00:05:35,377 --> 00:05:36,169
What, nothing.

63
00:05:36,169 --> 00:05:37,671
A radio.

64
00:05:37,671 --> 00:05:38,964
-You little thief!

65
00:05:38,964 --> 00:05:41,633
We didn't spend 15 years
feeding and clothings you

66
00:05:41,633 --> 00:05:43,802
so you could go and
steal car radios.

67
00:05:43,802 --> 00:05:45,220
-I didn't steal
it, Ma, all right?

68
00:05:45,220 --> 00:05:48,640
I bought it off for 10 bucks and
tomorrow I'll sell it for 25.

69
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:49,599
-Now you see?

70
00:05:49,599 --> 00:05:51,101
Is that what you
want to stay here,

71
00:05:51,101 --> 00:05:54,104
so we can raise the future star
of "America's Most Wanted"?

72
00:05:54,104 --> 00:05:55,522
FRANK: What are you
getting so upset about?

73
00:05:55,522 --> 00:05:57,274
He just told you you
he didn't steal it.

74
00:05:57,274 --> 00:05:59,568
You know, that's the way
things are done here.

75
00:05:59,568 --> 00:06:01,111
You know, you buy low
and you tell high.

76
00:06:01,111 --> 00:06:03,363
-Oh to hell with your
high and your low.

77
00:06:03,363 --> 00:06:08,577
Frank, I want that piece
of junk out of here.

78
00:06:08,577 --> 00:06:12,914
-Hey, Ricky, I'll give
you $12.50 for it.

79
00:06:12,914 --> 00:06:14,416
-Come on, Pop, what
do you want it for?

80
00:06:14,416 --> 00:06:15,709
You don't even
have a car anymore.

81
00:06:15,709 --> 00:06:17,794
-Hey it's not like I'm
going to be without a car

82
00:06:17,794 --> 00:06:19,170
the rest of my life.

83
00:06:19,170 --> 00:06:21,256
Soon as this place turns around,
the first thing I'm going to do

84
00:06:21,256 --> 00:06:24,384
is I'm going to buy
my old Chevy back.

85
00:06:24,384 --> 00:06:26,970
Look, you see?

86
00:06:26,970 --> 00:06:29,347
You see the kind of clientele
this place can attract?

87
00:06:29,347 --> 00:06:31,850
Huh?

88
00:06:31,850 --> 00:06:33,226
Welcome to our restaurant.

89
00:06:33,226 --> 00:06:34,769
Would you prefer a window table?

90
00:06:38,607 --> 00:06:39,983
-Hi, Dad.

91
00:06:39,983 --> 00:06:40,817
It's me.

92
00:06:40,817 --> 00:06:41,568
-Nydia!

93
00:06:44,654 --> 00:06:45,405
-Hi, Ricky.

94
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:51,828
Hi, Mom.

95
00:06:57,751 --> 00:06:59,169
-What did you do to your hair?

96
00:06:59,169 --> 00:07:01,087
-I dyed it, do you like it?

97
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:02,797
We brought you back
from Puerto Rico

98
00:07:02,797 --> 00:07:05,216
so you could get an
American education,

99
00:07:05,216 --> 00:07:07,510
not so you could turn into
Marilyn Monroe, Nydia.

100
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:08,428
-Oh, Ma.

101
00:07:08,428 --> 00:07:10,472
Stop being so dramatic.

102
00:07:10,472 --> 00:07:11,806
Everybody's doing this.

103
00:07:11,806 --> 00:07:14,059
-Who cares what
color her hair is?

104
00:07:14,059 --> 00:07:16,811
The important thing is
she's back home with us.

105
00:07:16,811 --> 00:07:19,022
Now we can go to
the movies and go

106
00:07:19,022 --> 00:07:21,024
ice skating at
Rockefeller Center.

107
00:07:21,024 --> 00:07:23,693
-Oh no, I'm sorry, Daddy,
I'm only here for a few days.

108
00:07:23,693 --> 00:07:24,527
Listen.

109
00:07:24,527 --> 00:07:27,822
I met this guy.

110
00:07:27,822 --> 00:07:30,408
He's a medical student
at Harvard University,

111
00:07:30,408 --> 00:07:33,620
and he wants me to meet
his parents on the Cape.

112
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:34,871
-The Cape.

113
00:07:34,871 --> 00:07:36,539
-It's just this place where
they have a vacation--

114
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:37,916
-We know where the
Cape is, all right?

115
00:07:37,916 --> 00:07:39,876
You always talk to us like
we're a bunch of bumpkins.

116
00:07:39,876 --> 00:07:43,421
-Well in your case, that
would be about eight steps up.

117
00:07:43,421 --> 00:07:44,673
-Yeah well you're
the one that sounds

118
00:07:44,673 --> 00:07:46,508
like you just got
off some banana boat.

119
00:07:46,508 --> 00:07:47,884
Look I gotta get
out of here, I think

120
00:07:47,884 --> 00:07:49,260
my stomach is going to be fixed.

121
00:07:49,260 --> 00:07:51,513
-You take that radio and
you get the $10 back,

122
00:07:51,513 --> 00:07:52,555
you hear me, Ricky?

123
00:07:52,555 --> 00:07:54,557
-Listen, I promised
Chris I'd call him.

124
00:07:54,557 --> 00:07:58,061
We'll talk some more later, OK?

125
00:07:58,061 --> 00:08:01,690
You look beautiful.

126
00:08:01,690 --> 00:08:03,942
Oh, Daddy, everything has
gotten so expensive up there.

127
00:08:03,942 --> 00:08:09,322
I'm going to need another
$2,000 when I leave, OK?

128
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:10,115
-$2,000?

129
00:08:10,115 --> 00:08:11,074
Did she that?

130
00:08:11,074 --> 00:08:12,534
Where am I going to get $2,000?

131
00:08:12,534 --> 00:08:13,868
-You're asking me?

132
00:08:13,868 --> 00:08:15,829
You're the one who created
little Ms. Frankenstein

133
00:08:15,829 --> 00:08:17,872
by never telling
her what is really

134
00:08:17,872 --> 00:08:19,499
going on around here, Frank.

135
00:08:19,499 --> 00:08:21,167
-What's so wrong with that, huh?

136
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:23,169
I want her to grow up
without worrying about money

137
00:08:23,169 --> 00:08:25,630
and I want her to grow
up with confidence.

138
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:28,341
You know, in one
more year she's going

139
00:08:28,341 --> 00:08:30,552
to be the only member of
either of our families

140
00:08:30,552 --> 00:08:32,429
to have graduated from college.

141
00:08:32,429 --> 00:08:34,472
-That's great, she'll be
the first college graduate,

142
00:08:34,472 --> 00:08:36,141
and I'll be the first
one in my family

143
00:08:36,141 --> 00:08:38,435
that ever has to go
on welfare, right?

144
00:08:38,435 --> 00:08:41,521
-Nobody's going on welfare
in this family, OK?

145
00:08:44,858 --> 00:08:46,443
MANNY: I could get you
22 of these, all right?

146
00:08:46,443 --> 00:08:49,070
Blue, green, or maroon?

147
00:08:49,070 --> 00:08:50,113
-What about gray?

148
00:08:50,113 --> 00:08:52,323
You know, my wife,
she likes gray.

149
00:08:52,323 --> 00:08:53,575
-You don't want gray.

150
00:08:53,575 --> 00:08:55,201
Take a look around, huh?

151
00:08:55,201 --> 00:08:56,745
See any gray around here?

152
00:08:56,745 --> 00:08:58,747
These are tropical people.

153
00:08:58,747 --> 00:09:01,082
We're talking maroon, we're
talking green like vegetation.

154
00:09:01,082 --> 00:09:05,086
Blue, like the sky or the ocean.

155
00:09:05,086 --> 00:09:06,588
When I got you all
those suitcases

156
00:09:06,588 --> 00:09:08,089
and you couldn't
move them all, huh?

157
00:09:08,089 --> 00:09:10,717
Didn't I take the
rest of them back?

158
00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:12,802
You're going to have
to trust me on this.

159
00:09:12,802 --> 00:09:14,304
You're going to
take 22 of these.

160
00:09:14,304 --> 00:09:15,472
I guarantee you're
moving them out

161
00:09:15,472 --> 00:09:17,390
of here in four weeks, tops.

162
00:09:17,390 --> 00:09:19,476
I'll even throw in a gray
suit, free of charge all right,

163
00:09:19,476 --> 00:09:22,771
so you can wear it around the
house and make your wife happy.

164
00:09:22,771 --> 00:09:24,314
-Double breasted.

165
00:09:24,314 --> 00:09:26,816
My wife, she likes
double breasted.

166
00:09:26,816 --> 00:09:29,027
-I'll see what I can do, OK?

167
00:09:29,027 --> 00:09:30,779
You think the two of
these on consignment,

168
00:09:30,779 --> 00:09:34,949
we'll settle up when I bring
the rest in a couple days.

169
00:09:34,949 --> 00:09:39,287
[speaking spanish]

170
00:09:39,287 --> 00:09:41,456
-Got the radios here,
radios right here, c'mon.

171
00:09:41,456 --> 00:09:44,000
Let's go, ladies and gentlemen,
we got radios here. $40,

172
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,084
all sales are final.

173
00:09:45,084 --> 00:09:46,211
Radios, radios, radios.

174
00:09:46,211 --> 00:09:48,505
Radios are right here,
radios are right here.

175
00:09:48,505 --> 00:09:50,590
Let's go.

176
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:52,842
Ladies and gentlemen.

177
00:09:52,842 --> 00:09:53,927
Radios, radios.

178
00:09:53,927 --> 00:09:55,303
-What are you guys doing?

179
00:09:55,303 --> 00:09:56,805
-Man, we're trying to get paid.

180
00:09:56,805 --> 00:09:57,764
-You best show some respect.

181
00:09:57,764 --> 00:09:58,640
Relax.

182
00:09:58,640 --> 00:09:59,808
Hey, do you want a radio?

183
00:09:59,808 --> 00:10:00,809
-No, forget about it.

184
00:10:00,809 --> 00:10:01,851
You know Manny only goes legit.

185
00:10:01,851 --> 00:10:02,644
-Right, right.

186
00:10:02,644 --> 00:10:03,853
-Yeah, you know what?

187
00:10:03,853 --> 00:10:05,480
I bet you pay all sorts of
taxes for that stuff you

188
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:06,564
get over in the
Garment District.

189
00:10:06,564 --> 00:10:08,149
-Yeah, I pay taxes all
right, and you guys

190
00:10:08,149 --> 00:10:09,526
are going to get
yourselves busted.

191
00:10:09,526 --> 00:10:10,902
-No one's going to get busted.

192
00:10:10,902 --> 00:10:14,364
Man, just yesterday, I sold a
cop a blown one for $50, man.

193
00:10:14,364 --> 00:10:15,532
Come on.

194
00:10:15,532 --> 00:10:16,241
-Let me see that.

195
00:10:19,536 --> 00:10:20,703
All right, I'll
give you $20 for it.

196
00:10:20,703 --> 00:10:21,996
-Nah, just forget
about it, all right?

197
00:10:21,996 --> 00:10:23,998
Why don't you just go
to Macy's and pay $200,

198
00:10:23,998 --> 00:10:25,875
that way you can get yourself
a warranty and everything?

199
00:10:25,875 --> 00:10:26,668
-All right.

200
00:10:26,668 --> 00:10:27,377
Here's your $40.

201
00:10:30,755 --> 00:10:31,506
-This is--

202
00:10:35,718 --> 00:10:37,387
-You better explain to
these coconut-eaten punks

203
00:10:37,387 --> 00:10:38,721
who runs this neighborhood.

204
00:10:43,226 --> 00:10:44,561
-Now listen.

205
00:10:44,561 --> 00:10:46,396
You little punks are going to
have to learn early that you

206
00:10:46,396 --> 00:10:47,647
don't do nothing in
this neighborhood

207
00:10:47,647 --> 00:10:48,982
without giving me my cut, eh?

208
00:10:48,982 --> 00:10:49,732
Capisce?

209
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:57,574
I'll blind you, I'll blind you,
you do that again you little--

210
00:10:57,574 --> 00:11:00,243
-C'mon, you know better.

211
00:11:00,243 --> 00:11:01,828
-Y'all can't be doing that shit.

212
00:11:01,828 --> 00:11:05,081
How come you don't
have to pay him?

213
00:11:05,081 --> 00:11:06,875
-Put it down.

214
00:11:06,875 --> 00:11:08,001
Put it down, Loco.

215
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:13,006
-Everybody pays him.

216
00:11:13,006 --> 00:11:13,923
Come here.

217
00:11:13,923 --> 00:11:15,884
I got to talk to you.

218
00:11:15,884 --> 00:11:17,260
-Damn.

219
00:11:17,260 --> 00:11:18,928
MANNY: Look, Ricky, I want you
to forget about that guy, OK?

220
00:11:18,928 --> 00:11:20,179
His days are numbered anyway.

221
00:11:20,179 --> 00:11:21,431
-What do you mean?

222
00:11:21,431 --> 00:11:22,765
-Hey, he's been skimming
off some fence, they think.

223
00:11:22,765 --> 00:11:23,933
Word on the street
is that they're

224
00:11:23,933 --> 00:11:25,602
going to put the hit
on him any day now.

225
00:11:25,602 --> 00:11:27,103
Maybe you should introduce
me to these guys,

226
00:11:27,103 --> 00:11:29,606
because I hit that
fat pig myself.

227
00:11:29,606 --> 00:11:31,107
Ricky.

228
00:11:31,107 --> 00:11:33,860
I wrote your sister a couple
times, she hasn't answered me.

229
00:11:33,860 --> 00:11:35,737
You heard anything from her?

230
00:11:35,737 --> 00:11:36,779
-Hey look, Manny.

231
00:11:36,779 --> 00:11:38,114
You're all right, you're
always looking out

232
00:11:38,114 --> 00:11:40,742
for me and everything, so
I'm going to do you a solid.

233
00:11:40,742 --> 00:11:42,744
You don't want any
of that anymore.

234
00:11:42,744 --> 00:11:43,703
-Why?

235
00:11:43,703 --> 00:11:45,455
-Because she's
buggin', that's why.

236
00:11:45,455 --> 00:11:46,414
You should see her, man.

237
00:11:46,414 --> 00:11:47,457
I think they
short-circuited her up

238
00:11:47,457 --> 00:11:48,666
in that college or something.

239
00:11:48,666 --> 00:11:49,959
-When did you see her?

240
00:11:49,959 --> 00:11:51,169
You went to Boston?

241
00:11:51,169 --> 00:11:52,545
-Nah, man, she's home.

242
00:11:52,545 --> 00:11:54,464
Look, I got to get back before
they think I split on them.

243
00:11:54,464 --> 00:11:55,298
I'll catch you later.

244
00:11:55,298 --> 00:11:56,716
-Yeah, OK.

245
00:11:56,716 --> 00:11:58,509
All right.

246
00:11:58,509 --> 00:11:59,719
-Listen.

247
00:11:59,719 --> 00:12:02,388
I talked to Chris and he
said his family is really

248
00:12:02,388 --> 00:12:04,515
looking forward to meeting me.

249
00:12:04,515 --> 00:12:05,808
-Yeah, how about us?

250
00:12:05,808 --> 00:12:07,518
When do we get to me him?

251
00:12:07,518 --> 00:12:10,355
-Um, uh, sure, I'll see if
I can work something out.

252
00:12:13,608 --> 00:12:15,360
I can't believe you guys
are still buying this stuff.

253
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:17,153
Don't you have any arugula?

254
00:12:17,153 --> 00:12:18,655
-Arugula what?

255
00:12:18,655 --> 00:12:20,573
-Or romaine, even?

256
00:12:20,573 --> 00:12:21,449
