a little curious

1057
00:43:43,371 --> 00:43:44,872
about where that guy got hit?

1058
00:43:44,872 --> 00:43:47,291
-Maybe we ought to give
people more credit.

1059
00:43:47,291 --> 00:43:49,168
-Man!

1060
00:43:49,168 --> 00:43:51,629
I'm jinxed is what it is.

1061
00:43:51,629 --> 00:43:53,381
That's it, you know.

1062
00:43:53,381 --> 00:43:56,259
I have no more ideas.

1063
00:43:56,259 --> 00:43:57,260
Go ahead.

1064
00:43:57,260 --> 00:43:58,928
Call your brother.

1065
00:43:58,928 --> 00:44:01,013
Tell him he was right all along.

1066
00:44:01,013 --> 00:44:03,140
Tell them what a big
disappointment I turned out

1067
00:44:03,140 --> 00:44:05,560
to be, and that if
he'll put us up I,

1068
00:44:05,560 --> 00:44:07,770
I promise to keep my
head down whenever

1069
00:44:07,770 --> 00:44:09,897
he walks into the room.

1070
00:44:09,897 --> 00:44:11,065
-I don't understand
why you always

1071
00:44:11,065 --> 00:44:14,151
gotta be comparing
yourself to my brother for.

1072
00:44:14,151 --> 00:44:17,029
At least you tried
to do something.

1073
00:44:17,029 --> 00:44:18,406
You worked your way
up from a dishwasher,

1074
00:44:18,406 --> 00:44:21,409
and you opened up
your own restaurant.

1075
00:44:21,409 --> 00:44:24,370
And you put your daughter
through three years of college.

1076
00:44:24,370 --> 00:44:26,497
How many people do we know
over there who can say that?

1077
00:44:29,458 --> 00:44:31,377
-You really mean that?

1078
00:44:31,377 --> 00:44:32,461
-I said it didn't I?

1079
00:44:36,424 --> 00:44:40,845
[knocking]

1080
00:44:40,845 --> 00:44:43,264
-Gilberto, I don't
have the money.

1081
00:44:43,264 --> 00:44:44,265
OK?

1082
00:44:44,265 --> 00:44:45,766
I'm working on
getting you the money.

1083
00:44:45,766 --> 00:44:46,601
OK?
-No.

1084
00:44:46,601 --> 00:44:47,393
Listen, Frank.

1085
00:44:47,393 --> 00:44:48,519
I heard about what happened.

1086
00:44:48,519 --> 00:44:50,187
And with all the news
coverage and everything.

1087
00:44:50,187 --> 00:44:52,356
And I figured you're
going to be needing

1088
00:44:52,356 --> 00:44:54,775
a lot more groceries
from now on.

1089
00:44:54,775 --> 00:44:57,111
Anything you need--
and I mean anything--

1090
00:44:57,111 --> 00:44:58,863
you just come to my store.

1091
00:44:58,863 --> 00:44:59,989
Is that OK?

1092
00:44:59,989 --> 00:45:01,407
-Well, thanks.

1093
00:45:01,407 --> 00:45:04,785
