1135
00:46:25,199 --> 00:46:26,200
-He was right here!

1136
00:46:26,200 --> 00:46:26,993
He was over here!

1137
00:46:26,993 --> 00:46:29,203
Right here.

1138
00:46:29,203 --> 00:46:31,163
He was right here!

1139
00:46:31,163 --> 00:46:32,164
And right here too.

1140
00:46:32,164 --> 00:46:33,165
He stumbled.

1141
00:46:33,165 --> 00:46:33,958
He got shot over here.

1142
00:46:33,958 --> 00:46:34,750
He went here.

1143
00:46:34,750 --> 00:46:35,710
He went here.

1144
00:46:35,710 --> 00:46:39,588
He was a big, fat,
disgusting guy.

1145
00:46:39,588 --> 00:46:41,007
-Give me what he had
before they did him in.

1146
00:46:46,679 --> 00:46:47,722
-I'm telling you everybody!

1147
00:46:47,722 --> 00:46:51,559
He was a big, fat,
disgusting criminal.

1148
00:46:51,559 --> 00:46:53,686
He was all over this restaurant.

1149
00:46:53,686 --> 00:46:56,480
Give me my pants.

1150
00:46:56,480 --> 00:46:57,773
-Chris.

1151
00:46:57,773 --> 00:47:00,026
Chris I have some
very good news.

1152
00:47:00,026 --> 00:47:02,069
Mother's doing
much, much better.

1153
00:47:02,069 --> 00:47:03,863
And I think I'll
be able to leave

1154
00:47:03,863 --> 00:47:05,823
Argentina in a couple of days.

1155
00:47:05,823 --> 00:47:06,615
Isn't that just wonderful?

1156
00:47:09,535 --> 00:47:10,828
The doctor is assigning
a nurse to stay

1157
00:47:10,828 --> 00:47:14,248
with my mother for
the next few weeks.

1158
00:47:14,248 --> 00:47:16,000
He feels the chances
of her having

1159
00:47:16,000 --> 00:47:18,210
another stroke are minimal.

1160
00:47:18,210 --> 00:47:22,882
Even mother feels there
is no need for me to stay.

1161
00:47:22,882 --> 00:47:27,344
Yeah, she really
is just wonderful.

1162
00:47:27,344 --> 00:47:31,307
[giggles]

1163
00:47:31,307 --> 00:47:35,144
Ma, since the restaurant
is doing much better now,

1164
00:47:35,144 --> 00:47:37,938
can I have some money to
get my hair touched up?

1165
00:47:37,938 --> 00:47:41,275
I mean, look at this.

1166
00:47:41,275 --> 00:47:42,485
-Nydia, you have
such beautiful hair.

1167
00:47:42,485 --> 00:47:44,153
Why don't you just get one
of those short haircuts

1168
00:47:44,153 --> 00:47:45,780
until it grows back out.

1169
00:47:45,780 --> 00:47:48,616
-'Cause I like it this way.

1170
00:47:48,616 --> 00:47:50,493
So do we have any
extra money or not?

1171
00:47:50,493 --> 00:47:51,786
-Nydia?

1172
00:47:51,786 --> 00:47:54,121
-Hm?

1173
00:47:54,121 --> 00:47:56,457
-Is there anything
you want to tell me?

1174
00:47:56,457 --> 00:47:57,917
-Like what?

1175
00:47:57,917 --> 00:47:59,919
-I don't know like do I
have any terrible diseases

1176
00:47:59,919 --> 00:48:01,670
I don't know anything about?

1177
00:48:01,670 --> 00:48:03,130
-What are you talking about?

1178
00:48:03,130 --> 00:48:06,467
-I'm talking about me having
relapses, and needing nurses,

1179
00:48:06,467 --> 00:48:08,803
and you having to
leave Argentina.

1180
00:48:08,803 --> 00:48:10,304
When the hell were you
ever in Argentina, Nydia?

1181
00:48:13,307 --> 00:48:15,309
-I can't believe this.

1182
00:48:15,309 --> 00:48:17,686
You've been spying on me?

1183
00:48:17,686 --> 00:48:19,814
-Hey, don't try and
turn this thing around.

1184
00:48:19,814 --> 00:48:22,399
OK? 'Cause I was innocently
walking to my room

1185
00:48:22,399 --> 00:48:23,943
when I heard some
person I didn't

1186
00:48:23,943 --> 00:48:25,861
know talking on your telephone.

1187
00:48:25,861 --> 00:48:29,448
Nydia, I'm going
to say this once.

1188
00:48:29,448 --> 00:48:32,368
You better start telling me
what's going on, because I

1189
00:48:32,368 --> 00:48:34,328
swear, money or no
money, you're not

1190
00:48:34,328 --> 00:48:36,413
going back to that
Boston University.

1191
00:48:36,413 --> 00:48:38,082
-You want me to tell
you what's going on?

1192
00:48:38,082 --> 00:48:38,916
-Yeah!

1193
00:48:38,916 --> 00:48:41,585
-Fine, I'll tell you all right.

1194
00:48:41,585 --> 00:48:42,336
I'll tell you.

1195
00:48:45,881 --> 00:48:48,926
I met Chris at a
party at Harvard.

1196
00:48:48,926 --> 00:48:52,680
His father is one of the
top surgeons in Boston.

1197
00:48:52,680 --> 00:48:54,348
His uncle is also a
doctor who teaches

1198
00:48:54,348 --> 00:48:55,558
at Harvard Medical School.

1199
00:48:58,519 --> 00:49:05,234
First, I told one little lie
to cover my stupid accent.

1200
00:49:05,234 --> 00:49:09,071
And then I had to tell another
lie to cover the first one.

1201
00:49:09,071 --> 00:49:13,576
And anyway, I'm sure you
know how the rest goes.

1202
00:49:13,576 --> 00:49:18,038
By the end of two drinks,
he thinks I'm wealthy.

1203
00:49:18,038 --> 00:49:19,707
And then when Dad said I
couldn't go to the Cape

1204
00:49:19,707 --> 00:49:22,710
to meet his parents, I had to
make up this thing about having

1205
00:49:22,710 --> 00:49:25,045
to go home because
you were sick and now

1206
00:49:25,045 --> 00:49:27,923
we're staying in Argentina.

1207
00:49:27,923 --> 00:49:32,386
Mom, you have no idea
what it's like out there.

1208
00:49:32,386 --> 00:49:34,722
You don't know how many
times I've met guys up there,

1209
00:49:34,722 --> 00:49:37,016
and when I tell them
I'm Puerto Rican,

1210
00:49:37,016 --> 00:49:39,935
sooner or later they get
around to asking if I grew up

1211
00:49:39,935 --> 00:49:42,938
on welfare, and if I have
any relatives in jail.

1212
00:49:42,938 --> 00:49:45,941
And I'm not just talking
about the students, either.

1213
00:49:45,941 --> 00:49:47,526
Even the professors
treat you like

1214
00:49:47,526 --> 00:49:48,986
you're from Mars or something.

1215
00:49:48,986 --> 00:49:51,030
I just get a little bored with
being on display all the time,

1216
00:49:51,030 --> 00:49:52,072
OK?

1217
00:49:52,072 --> 00:49:53,240
-I never realized
going to go college

1218
00:49:53,240 --> 00:49:54,450
could be so traumatic, Nydia.

1219
00:49:54,450 --> 00:49:55,910
Maybe I ought to
take your tuition

1220
00:49:55,910 --> 00:49:57,953
and send you to a
psychiatrist instead.

1221
00:49:57,953 --> 00:49:58,913
-See?

1222
00:49:58,913 --> 00:50:01,582
That's just what
I'm talking about.

1223
00:50:01,582 --> 00:50:04,418
There's just no way you're
going to understand, mom.

1224
00:50:04,418 --> 00:50:06,837
-I heard you say that
I was over my stroke,

1225
00:50:06,837 --> 00:50:09,298
and that you were
leaving Argentina.

1226
00:50:09,298 --> 00:50:12,051
Does that mean you're
going to the Cape?

1227
00:50:12,051 --> 00:50:14,595
-Well, it seems the restaurant
is doing much better now.

1228
00:50:14,595 --> 00:50:17,348
-Hey, I thought you were
studying business over there.

1229
00:50:17,348 --> 00:50:20,309
This place has been practically
empty for almost a year.

1230
00:50:20,309 --> 00:50:21,143
What do you think?

1231
00:50:21,143 --> 00:50:22,978
Our problems are suddenly over?

1232
00:50:22,978 --> 00:50:25,439
We can't afford
to hire somebody!

1233
00:50:25,439 --> 00:50:28,400
We need you here to at least
help us wait on the tables!

1234
00:50:28,400 --> 00:50:30,194
[spanish] Come here.

1235
00:50:30,194 --> 00:50:32,947
Come here.

1236
00:50:32,947 --> 00:50:36,700
I want to show you
something really special.

1237
00:50:36,700 --> 00:50:38,035
Look at this.

1238
00:50:38,035 --> 00:50:40,537
Your father went out yesterday
and he put this on credit,

1239
00:50:40,537 --> 00:50:42,248
just so you could have
something nice to wear when

1240
00:50:42,248 --> 00:50:44,375
you're working in
the restaurant.

1241
00:50:44,375 --> 00:50:45,876
And I know it's not
exactly something

1242
00:50:45,876 --> 00:50:47,002
you would pick out for yourself.

1243
00:50:47,002 --> 00:50:48,796
But he's jumping up and
down because he thinks

1244
00:50:48,796 --> 00:50:50,130
you're spending the
holidays with us.

1245
00:50:50,130 --> 00:50:53,384
And as much as he sacrificed
to put you through college,

1246
00:50:53,384 --> 00:50:56,303
the least you can do is call
this rich boyfriend of yours

1247
00:50:56,303 --> 00:50:58,806
and tell him I had
another relapse.

1248
00:50:58,806 --> 00:51:01,475
And another thing, I may just be
some jibaro that went straight

1249
00:51:01,475 --> 00:51:03,477
from Puerto Rico
to Spanish Harlem,

1250
00:51:03,477 --> 00:51:06,146
but it seems to me that if this
guy was worth anything more

1251
00:51:06,146 --> 00:51:08,941
than just money, he would
appreciate you a million

1252
00:51:08,941 --> 00:51:11,151
times more for
who you really are

1253
00:51:11,151 --> 00:51:13,320
and what it is you're
trying to accomplish.

1254
00:51:13,320 --> 00:51:16,323
Instead of going around trying
to build a relationship based

1255
00:51:16,323 --> 00:51:19,201
on one of the biggest
whoppers I ever heard, Nydia.

1256
00:51:19,201 --> 00:51:20,953
-Chris is not like that, Mom.

1257
00:51:20,953 --> 00:51:23,664
Any day now I'm going
to tell him the truth.

1258
00:51:23,664 --> 00:51:25,207
I just need a little
more time so--

1259
00:51:25,207 --> 00:51:26,500
so he can get to know me better.

1260
00:51:26,500 --> 00:51:27,251
That's all!

1261
00:51:57,823 --> 00:51:58,615
-Boo.

1262
00:51:58,615 --> 00:52:02,077
-Oh, Manny.

1263
00:52:02,077 --> 00:52:05,080
-You know, you should let
Ricky help you with this stuff.

1264
00:52:05,080 --> 00:52:07,333
-He's busy helping
Frank at the restaurant.

1265
00:52:07,333 --> 00:52:08,751
We're doing a little
better now, you know.

1266
00:52:08,751 --> 00:52:09,752
-I heard.

1267
00:52:09,752 --> 00:52:12,129
-So Manny, what's
a matter for you?

1268
00:52:12,129 --> 00:52:14,798
All of a sudden you're too
good to come to the restaurant

1269
00:52:14,798 --> 00:52:15,591
anymore?

1270
00:52:15,591 --> 00:52:16,759
-Not at all.

1271
00:52:16,759 --> 00:52:17,551
You know how it is.

1272
00:52:17,551 --> 00:52:18,969
Sometimes you get busy.

1273
00:52:18,969 --> 00:52:20,387
And before you know
it, you don't even

1274
00:52:20,387 --> 00:52:22,056
have time to visit
your favorite people.

1275
00:52:22,056 --> 00:52:23,932
-So you should come anyway.

1276
00:52:23,932 --> 00:52:25,142
And don't worry about Nydia.

1277
00:52:25,142 --> 00:52:26,769
You know, she's just a
little confused right now.

1278
00:52:26,769 --> 00:52:27,603
-I don't know.

1279
00:52:27,603 --> 00:52:29,188
She seemed pretty clear to me.

1280
00:52:29,188 --> 00:52:29,980
-You talk to her?

1281
00:52:29,980 --> 00:52:30,773
-Yeah, yeah.

1282
00:52:30,773 --> 00:52:32,316
We talked on the phone.

1283
00:52:32,316 --> 00:52:34,485
Mostly I just listened.

