00:52:34,485 --> 00:52:35,402
-She told you about Harvard.

1285
00:52:35,402 --> 00:52:37,071
-Yeah.

1286
00:52:37,071 --> 00:52:39,907
And, uh, who's gonna
compete with that, right?

1287
00:52:39,907 --> 00:52:40,991
-Hmm.

1288
00:52:40,991 --> 00:52:42,409
-Listen, I-- I gotta
go finish something up.

1289
00:52:42,409 --> 00:52:43,243
Are you gonna be OK?

1290
00:52:43,243 --> 00:52:46,413
-Oh my god, I don't believe it.

1291
00:52:46,413 --> 00:52:50,167
You know, this is exactly
what I've been looking for.

1292
00:52:50,167 --> 00:52:51,752
But how am I gonna get
this big thing back

1293
00:52:51,752 --> 00:52:54,046
to the restaurant with all
these bags and everything?

1294
00:52:57,758 --> 00:53:02,596
[speaking spanish]

1295
00:53:02,596 --> 00:53:03,430
-Ma,where you been?

1296
00:53:03,430 --> 00:53:04,640
You see that crowd out there?

1297
00:53:04,640 --> 00:53:06,225
-Manny had to help me
pick up some things.

1298
00:53:06,225 --> 00:53:07,476
Put them over there,
would you, Manny.

1299
00:53:07,476 --> 00:53:08,560
Nydia!

1300
00:53:08,560 --> 00:53:10,312
Nydia!

1301
00:53:10,312 --> 00:53:11,230
-Hey Manny, come here.

1302
00:53:11,230 --> 00:53:11,939
Check this out.

1303
00:53:14,858 --> 00:53:15,901
So what do you think?

1304
00:53:18,529 --> 00:53:20,989
-I don't think the feet
are supposed to have toes.

1305
00:53:20,989 --> 00:53:22,616
-Oh yeah.

1306
00:53:22,616 --> 00:53:23,784
Yeah, maybe you're right.

1307
00:53:23,784 --> 00:53:24,785
-Hey, hey, Manny!

1308
00:53:24,785 --> 00:53:25,619
-Hey, Frank.

1309
00:53:25,619 --> 00:53:27,871
-Pretty exciting, huh?

1310
00:53:27,871 --> 00:53:30,624
Look at the size of that guy.

1311
00:53:30,624 --> 00:53:32,084
Yesterday we had
three tourists that

1312
00:53:32,084 --> 00:53:33,710
came here and laid
down to take pictures.

1313
00:53:33,710 --> 00:53:36,130
There was still
room for one more!

1314
00:53:36,130 --> 00:53:38,298
I think whoever did this
was a really bad shot

1315
00:53:38,298 --> 00:53:40,134
because that bullet
richocheted all over the place

1316
00:53:40,134 --> 00:53:41,135
before it got him.

1317
00:53:41,135 --> 00:53:42,636
Look, there's a bullet
hole over there.

1318
00:53:42,636 --> 00:53:43,762
There's a bullet
hole right there.

1319
00:53:43,762 --> 00:53:44,972
One over there.

1320
00:53:44,972 --> 00:53:46,181
And there's one right
above the door over there.

1321
00:53:46,181 --> 00:53:47,808
-Carmen, por favor,
I really have to go.

1322
00:53:47,808 --> 00:53:48,976
-No, no, no no, no.

1323
00:53:48,976 --> 00:53:50,519
Don't give me any of this
I have to go stuff, OK?

1324
00:53:50,519 --> 00:53:51,520
[speaking spanish] Frank.

1325
00:53:51,520 --> 00:53:53,814
He looks like he
hasn't eaten in months.

1326
00:53:53,814 --> 00:53:56,024
-Hey, don't look at me, because
you know when a Puerto Rican

1327
00:53:56,024 --> 00:53:59,570
woman decides to feed you, just
open up your mouth and chew!

1328
00:53:59,570 --> 00:54:00,988
-Eat.

1329
00:54:00,988 --> 00:54:02,322
-Welp, since you
put it that way.

1330
00:54:05,659 --> 00:54:06,785
NYDIA: I can't wear this dress.

1331
00:54:06,785 --> 00:54:08,162
Look at this.

1332
00:54:08,162 --> 00:54:09,538
My boobs are falling out!

1333
00:54:09,538 --> 00:54:11,665
FRANK: You look beautiful!

1334
00:54:11,665 --> 00:54:16,545
[music playing]

1335
00:54:36,356 --> 00:54:38,358
-[speaking spanish].

1336
00:54:38,358 --> 00:54:39,860
I knew it.

1337
00:54:39,860 --> 00:54:42,779
Why can't anybody tell
me when we have company?

1338
00:54:42,779 --> 00:54:46,825
-Because you're the only one
who considers Manny company.

1339
00:54:46,825 --> 00:54:49,912
-Look, I-- I was, uh--
I was leaving anyway.

1340
00:54:49,912 --> 00:54:50,746
-Manny, I'm sorry.

1341
00:54:50,746 --> 00:54:51,538
I didn't mean that.
-No.

1342
00:54:51,538 --> 00:54:52,748
Oh, please.

1343
00:54:52,748 --> 00:54:54,333
-It's just that you always
catch me by surprise.

1344
00:54:54,333 --> 00:54:55,918
-Yeah, well, I,
uh-- I guess I could

1345
00:54:55,918 --> 00:54:57,503
say the same thing about you.

1346
00:54:57,503 --> 00:54:58,462
-Uh, Manny.

1347
00:54:58,462 --> 00:55:00,005
I know this is kind
of last minute,

1348
00:55:00,005 --> 00:55:01,590
but we're gonna open soon.

1349
00:55:01,590 --> 00:55:04,843
Could you stay and help us out
just before we get started?

1350
00:55:04,843 --> 00:55:06,220
-What are you doing?

1351
00:55:06,220 --> 00:55:08,388
We can manage this.

1352
00:55:08,388 --> 00:55:11,850
Besides, I'm sure Manny
has a lot of things to do.

1353
00:55:11,850 --> 00:55:13,185
Don't you have something to do?

1354
00:55:15,854 --> 00:55:17,231
-No.

1355
00:55:17,231 --> 00:55:20,442
As a matter of fact I don't.

1356
00:55:20,442 --> 00:55:21,318
-(SARCASTIC) Fine.

1357
00:55:21,318 --> 00:55:22,402
Fine.

1358
00:55:22,402 --> 00:55:24,238
Is this how you want
to spend your evening.

1359
00:55:24,238 --> 00:55:24,947
OK.

1360
00:55:28,325 --> 00:55:29,618
You take tables
one through five,

1361
00:55:29,618 --> 00:55:31,870
and I'll take six through ten.

1362
00:55:31,870 --> 00:55:33,914
-And first of all, in case
you've already forgotten,

1363
00:55:33,914 --> 00:55:35,165
I've done this plenty
of times before,

1364
00:55:35,165 --> 00:55:36,667
so I don't need you
telling me what to do.

1365
00:55:36,667 --> 00:55:41,213
And secondly, I'm not
doing this for you.

1366
00:55:41,213 --> 00:55:43,757
I'm doing it for your parents.

1367
00:55:43,757 --> 00:55:48,845
-Well, now that that's settled,
I'll go check on the beans.

1368
00:55:48,845 --> 00:55:50,806
-Can I open up now?

1369
00:55:50,806 --> 00:55:51,598
-Go ahead.

1370
00:55:51,598 --> 00:55:52,516
Let them in.

1371
00:55:57,729 --> 00:55:58,522
-Bienvenidos.

1372
00:55:58,522 --> 00:56:00,274
Welcome.

1373
00:56:00,274 --> 00:56:02,734
Hello, and welcome
to the Mambo Cafe.

1374
00:56:02,734 --> 00:56:04,945
Today's special is
Nydia's chuletas.

1375
00:56:04,945 --> 00:56:06,280
-Yeah, yeah, yeah, whatever.

1376
00:56:06,280 --> 00:56:08,907
You know that we've been outside
in the cold for 20 minutes?

1377
00:56:08,907 --> 00:56:10,784
When the hell are
we gonna sit down?

1378
00:56:10,784 --> 00:56:12,703
-Uh, Manny.

1379
00:56:12,703 --> 00:56:13,954
-Right away.

1380
00:56:13,954 --> 00:56:16,790
Nydia herself is going
to take care of you.

1381
00:56:16,790 --> 00:56:17,583
-Come with me, please.

1382
00:56:17,583 --> 00:56:18,959
-Hey.

1383
00:56:18,959 --> 00:56:22,212
And don't go putting us at a
table near the kitchen either!

1384
00:56:22,212 --> 00:56:23,297
-Hola.

1385
00:56:23,297 --> 00:56:30,804
We would like Una, mesa
for tres, por favor.

1386
00:56:30,804 --> 00:56:32,055
-Ah, si. [speaking spanish].

1387
00:56:32,055 --> 00:56:34,057
Why don't you come with me, eh?

1388
00:56:34,057 --> 00:56:37,227
I have, how do you say,
the perfect table for two.

1389
00:56:37,227 --> 00:56:38,186
-Oh!

1390
00:56:38,186 --> 00:56:38,937
-All right.

1391
00:56:43,525 --> 00:56:45,652
-This is Nydia.

1392
00:56:45,652 --> 00:56:49,531
She will, how do you say, will
be on honored to serve you.

1393
00:56:49,531 --> 00:56:50,616
-Oh.

1394
00:56:50,616 --> 00:56:51,450
Gracias.

1395
00:56:51,450 --> 00:56:52,409
-Thank-- thank you very much.

1396
00:56:52,409 --> 00:56:53,160
Thanks.

1397
00:56:56,788 --> 00:57:00,584
-Mommy, why is she wearing
that thing on her head?

1398
00:57:00,584 --> 00:57:05,339
-Honey, what did mommy
tell you about foreigners?

1399
00:57:05,339 --> 00:57:07,090
-That we should
stay away from them

1400
00:57:07,090 --> 00:57:08,967
because they have diseases?

1401
00:57:08,967 --> 00:57:10,177
-No.

1402
00:57:10,177 --> 00:57:11,678
-The other thing.

1403
00:57:11,678 --> 00:57:14,723
Sometimes they wear
colorful costumes

1404
00:57:14,723 --> 00:57:17,517
because they pray to gods
that are different than ours.

1405
00:57:20,437 --> 00:57:22,564
-Could you excuse me a second.

1406
00:57:22,564 --> 00:57:23,565
-Oh.

1407
00:57:23,565 --> 00:57:24,858
You speak English!

1408
00:57:29,196 --> 00:57:30,155
-[speaking spanish].

1409
00:57:30,155 --> 00:57:32,032
What the hell are you doing?

1410
00:57:32,032 --> 00:57:33,700
Is this why you stay?

1411
00:57:33,700 --> 00:57:34,785
To give me a hard time.

1412
00:57:34,785 --> 00:57:36,536
-Look, I'm sorry, OK?

1413
00:57:36,536 --> 00:57:38,705
It's just that you're
always so serious.

1414
00:57:38,705 --> 00:57:41,667
I-- I just thought it
might make you laugh.

1415
00:57:41,667 --> 00:57:44,378
-Make me laugh?

1416
00:57:44,378 --> 00:57:47,214
Look at the way I'm dressed.

1417
00:57:47,214 --> 00:57:50,967
I wear business suits and
carry a brief case in Boston.

1418
00:57:50,967 --> 00:57:52,844
And those people
over there think

1419
00:57:52,844 --> 00:57:54,721
that I'm dressed like
this to pray to gods.

1420
00:57:59,726 --> 00:58:00,769
What's the hell is so funny?

1421
00:58:03,855 --> 00:58:04,564
-Nothing.

1422
00:58:07,526 --> 00:58:08,735
-Just forget about it, OK?

1423
00:58:14,241 --> 00:58:16,910
Sorry, we had a
slight emergency.

1424
00:58:16,910 --> 00:58:18,787
Uh, have you had a chance
to look at the menu?

1425
00:58:18,787 --> 00:58:19,579
-Ah, yes.

1426
00:58:19,579 --> 00:58:20,747
Yes.

1427
00:58:20,747 --> 00:58:24,251
Can you tell me, what
is Fat Tony's last meal?

1428
00:58:24,251 --> 00:58:26,753
-Isn't my wife incredible?

1429
00:58:26,753 --> 00:58:29,506
One day she's in this
country and already she

1430
00:58:29,506 --> 00:58:31,591
speaks perfect English.

1431
00:58:31,591 --> 00:58:33,927
-Isn't there something
you should be doing?

1432
00:58:33,927 --> 00:58:35,137
-I got-- of course.

1433
00:58:35,137 --> 00:58:36,263
How stupid of me.

1434
00:58:36,263 --> 00:58:38,598
This is our favorite song.

1435
00:58:38,598 --> 00:58:41,810
We must dance.

1436
00:58:41,810 --> 00:58:42,561
-They're gonna dance!

1437
00:58:47,607 --> 00:58:53,029
[music playing]

1438
00:59:34,821 --> 00:59:35,864
-See?

1439
00:59:35,864 --> 00:59:38,325
This is exactly why
I love these Latins.

1440
00:59:41,912 --> 00:59:44,164
The world could be
falling down around them,

1441
00:59:44,164 --> 00:59:46,583
and all they want
to do is dance!

1442
00:59:58,053 --> 01:00:04,267
[bells ringing]

1443
01:00:04,267 --> 01:00:05,477
MAN ON STREET: I'm
thinking of goin'

1444
01:00:05,477 --> 01:00:06,853
