1445
01:00:06,853 --> 01:00:08,438
SECOND MAN ON STREET: I
wan going down to Miami.

1446
01:00:08,438 --> 01:00:10,440
MAN ON STREET: Oh really?

1447
01:00:10,440 --> 01:00:12,400
It's hot over there.

1448
01:00:12,400 --> 01:00:13,819
You know, so I don't know.

1449
01:00:16,404 --> 01:00:18,198
-Listen, Joey.

1450
01:00:18,198 --> 01:00:20,033
I just want to
thank you for taking

1451
01:00:20,033 --> 01:00:22,410
care of that Fat Tony problem.

1452
01:00:22,410 --> 01:00:26,248
I know me and him were--
we grew up together.

1453
01:00:26,248 --> 01:00:30,126
He was nine years old and we
shook down our first tourists

1454
01:00:30,126 --> 01:00:32,796
right over there on 5th Street.

1455
01:00:32,796 --> 01:00:37,217
And that son of a bitch--
that greedy, ungrateful,

1456
01:00:37,217 --> 01:00:39,052
double-crossing
son of a bitch, he

1457
01:00:39,052 --> 01:00:40,345
had the nerve to steal from me.

1458
01:00:43,598 --> 01:00:48,061
Anyway, I want to thank you.

1459
01:00:48,061 --> 01:00:51,064
I owe you.

1460
01:00:51,064 --> 01:00:53,567
Now, thank you.

1461
01:00:53,567 --> 01:00:56,486
-[italian]

1462
01:01:12,002 --> 01:01:13,837
Remember that Fat Tony thing?

1463
01:01:13,837 --> 01:01:15,714
-Yeah, what about it, Joey?

1464
01:01:15,714 --> 01:01:17,924
-I always thought Angelo
took care of him-- you know,

1465
01:01:17,924 --> 01:01:21,177
Fat Tony being his
cousin and whatnot.

1466
01:01:21,177 --> 01:01:23,847
-Yeah, we too.

1467
01:01:23,847 --> 01:01:26,099
-So how come just
now Angelo comes up

1468
01:01:26,099 --> 01:01:29,185
and thanks me for
taking care of him?

1469
01:01:29,185 --> 01:01:31,605
-I don't know, Joey.

1470
01:01:31,605 --> 01:01:33,940
-I want you two to see what
you can find out about him.

1471
01:01:33,940 --> 01:01:36,568
And don't say squat
to nobody, you hear?

1472
01:01:36,568 --> 01:01:37,360
-Yeah.

1473
01:01:37,360 --> 01:01:38,445
We got it covered, Joey.

1474
01:01:38,445 --> 01:01:40,071
Don't worry about it.

1475
01:01:40,071 --> 01:01:40,780
-[speaking spanish].

1476
01:01:49,998 --> 01:01:51,833
-And you said that
you, uh, you read

1477
01:01:51,833 --> 01:01:53,960
about this place in
the "New Yorker"?

1478
01:01:53,960 --> 01:01:55,503
-It wasn't exactly
"The New Yorker,"

1479
01:01:55,503 --> 01:01:57,505
but what's the difference?

1480
01:01:57,505 --> 01:01:58,840
Every time you
guys come to town,

1481
01:01:58,840 --> 01:02:00,508
we go to some
boring Broadway play

1482
01:02:00,508 --> 01:02:02,594
and then over to Joe Allen's.

1483
01:02:02,594 --> 01:02:04,471
I just thought you'd
appreciate something

1484
01:02:04,471 --> 01:02:06,932
different for a change.

1485
01:02:06,932 --> 01:02:10,810
-It looks fine to me.

1486
01:02:10,810 --> 01:02:15,398
-[speaking spanish]

1487
01:02:27,243 --> 01:02:30,455
-Here you go, and someone
will be with you shortly.

1488
01:02:30,455 --> 01:02:31,247
-Come.

1489
01:02:31,247 --> 01:02:34,125
Come, come.

1490
01:02:34,125 --> 01:02:35,585
-Jesus, Ma!

1491
01:02:35,585 --> 01:02:37,170
You forgot the tostones again!

1492
01:02:37,170 --> 01:02:38,588
-I can't be expected
to remember everything.

1493
01:02:38,588 --> 01:02:39,547
-[speaking spanish]

1494
01:02:39,547 --> 01:02:40,215
-They're right there
in front of you!

1495
01:02:40,215 --> 01:02:41,508
-[speaking spanish]

1496
01:02:41,508 --> 01:02:43,176
-And you, when you finish
playing Ricardo Montalban,

1497
01:02:43,176 --> 01:02:44,970
could you give me a hand
in the kitchen, please!

1498
01:02:44,970 --> 01:02:45,929
-Hey Ricky.

1499
01:02:45,929 --> 01:02:47,138
You gotta bus
table number seven.

1500
01:02:50,558 --> 01:02:51,851
-Welcome to Mambo Cafe.

1501
01:02:51,851 --> 01:02:54,062
Uh, can I get you something
to drink before you start?

1502
01:02:54,062 --> 01:02:54,854
-Yup.

1503
01:02:54,854 --> 01:02:58,149
I'd like a water.

1504
01:02:58,149 --> 01:03:00,402
-Chris?

1505
01:03:00,402 --> 01:03:03,446
Just what are you doing here?

1506
01:03:03,446 --> 01:03:05,323
-What am I doing here?

1507
01:03:05,323 --> 01:03:07,200
What am I doing here?

1508
01:03:07,200 --> 01:03:10,578
You're supposed to be in-- in
Argentina, for Christ's sake.

1509
01:03:10,578 --> 01:03:12,414
What about your sick mother?

1510
01:03:12,414 --> 01:03:16,543
--[speaking spanish] I'm
your mother, not your slave.

1511
01:03:16,543 --> 01:03:17,669
Remember to pick up your orders.

1512
01:03:17,669 --> 01:03:19,337
I can't keep bringing
them out here for you.

1513
01:03:19,337 --> 01:03:20,046
Here.

1514
01:03:23,550 --> 01:03:25,051
-Oh my god.

1515
01:03:25,051 --> 01:03:26,845
I can explain this.

1516
01:03:26,845 --> 01:03:29,139
See, I was going to tell you.

1517
01:03:29,139 --> 01:03:30,390
It's just that-- uh.

1518
01:03:30,390 --> 01:03:31,224
-Chris.

1519
01:03:31,224 --> 01:03:35,979
Who is this person?

1520
01:03:35,979 --> 01:03:40,233
-Dad, this is Nydia.

1521
01:03:40,233 --> 01:03:44,529
Nydia, this is my father and
my mother and my sister Stacy.

1522
01:03:44,529 --> 01:03:45,363
-Hi, Nydia.

1523
01:03:45,363 --> 01:03:46,281
-Hi.

1524
01:03:46,281 --> 01:03:49,451
It's a pleasure to
meet all of you.

1525
01:03:49,451 --> 01:03:50,577
Listen, Chris.

1526
01:03:50,577 --> 01:03:52,746
I can explain this, OK?

1527
01:03:52,746 --> 01:03:53,830
-Let me get this straight.

1528
01:03:53,830 --> 01:03:56,833
This is the Nydia
we're supposed to meet?

1529
01:03:56,833 --> 01:03:59,961
-How did you say you two met?

1530
01:03:59,961 --> 01:04:01,254
-I'm getting another headache.

1531
01:04:01,254 --> 01:04:02,172
-Chr-- Chris!

1532
01:04:02,172 --> 01:04:03,715
Hold this, please.

1533
01:04:03,715 --> 01:04:05,550
Chris, wait a second.

1534
01:04:05,550 --> 01:04:08,011
Please, Chris, I
know how this looks.

1535
01:04:08,011 --> 01:04:10,638
But please, give me
a chance to explain.

1536
01:04:10,638 --> 01:04:11,765
-Nydia.

1537
01:04:11,765 --> 01:04:14,017
I don't understand how
you could do this to me?

1538
01:04:14,017 --> 01:04:15,185
